"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141945","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-08-07","<p>​The Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office commissioned a Joint Analysis of Conflict and Stability (JACS) in 2017 (refreshed in 2019) for the Western Balkans. A JACS is a strategic assessment used to strengthen cross-government approaches to tackling conflict and instability overseas. The analysis covered youth unemployment as well as migration and &quot;brain-drain&quot;. In addition, the Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office has commissioned analysis on 'The Cost of Youth Emigration from Serbia' and analysis by the British Council for the Conflict, Stability and Security Fund (CSSF).</p><p>Through the CSSF, the Government funds the following projects to help tackle unemployment in the Western Balkans:</p><ul><li><p>21st Century Schools; which will provide training to children in over 4,500 schools, to improve digital literacy and core skills across the Western Balkans.;</p></li><li><p>a project supporting employment and social services for vulnerable youths in Albania; and</p></li><li><p>in North Macedonia working jointly with the National Youth Council and IT Chamber of Commerce to support digital skills training to young people in return for community work.</p></li></ul>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","HL17487 ; HL17488 ; HL17490 ; HL17491","2019-08-07T14:56:10.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141945/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141945/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141945/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-07-24","Balkans: Overseas Aid","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what support they are providing to projects aimed at tackling unemployment and migration in the Western Balkans.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Sandwich",,"The Earl of Sandwich","HL17489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141946","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-08-07","<p>​The Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office commissioned a Joint Analysis of Conflict and Stability (JACS) in 2017 (refreshed in 2019) for the Western Balkans. A JACS is a strategic assessment used to strengthen cross-government approaches to tackling conflict and instability overseas. The analysis covered youth unemployment as well as migration and &quot;brain-drain&quot;. In addition, the Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office has commissioned analysis on 'The Cost of Youth Emigration from Serbia' and analysis by the British Council for the Conflict, Stability and Security Fund (CSSF).</p><p>Through the CSSF, the Government funds the following projects to help tackle unemployment in the Western Balkans:</p><ul><li><p>21st Century Schools; which will provide training to children in over 4,500 schools, to improve digital literacy and core skills across the Western Balkans.;</p></li><li><p>a project supporting employment and social services for vulnerable youths in Albania; and</p></li><li><p>in North Macedonia working jointly with the National Youth Council and IT Chamber of Commerce to support digital skills training to young people in return for community work.</p></li></ul>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","HL17487 ; HL17488 ; HL17489 ; HL17491","2019-08-07T14:56:10.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141946/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141946/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141946/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-07-24","Balkans: Overseas Aid","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many aid and development projects in the Western Balkans they support; through which (1) embassies, (2) governments, and (3) local organisations, that support is provided; and how much they have spent on such support.","false"